{"bookResponse":{"bookId":"2ad4ecbb8e24f6cd9efcac897a233cf2","locale":"en_US","title":"macOS User Guide","meta":{"productVersion":"13.0","platformOSVersion":"13.0","icon":"https://help.apple.com/assets/63BCA927AAE78C58DD7FBE35/63BCA92EAAE78C58DD7FBE76/en_US/058e4af8e726290f491044219d2eee73.png","build_date":"Wed Mar 22 20:19:57 GMT 2023","product":"mac-help","creationDate":"Fri Mar 24 07:00:00 GMT 2023","lastModifiedDate":"Mon Mar 27 17:01:20 GMT 2023","contentType":"book","framework":"duck-15.4.0:goose-2.15.4:cuckoo-4.2.0"},"tocId":"MH43558","bookInfo":{"versionsDetails":[{"productVersion":"14.0","displayVersion":"macOS Sonoma 14","platform":"mac","platformOSVersion":"14.0"},{"productVersion":"13.0","displayVersion":"macOS Ventura 13","platform":"mac","platformOSVersion":"13.0"},{"productVersion":"12.0","displayVersion":"macOS Monterey 12","platform":"mac","platformOSVersion":"12.0"}]},"articles":[{"articleId":{"id":"BK_2AD4ECBB8E24F6CD9EFCAC897A233CF2_MCHL67C83F41","locale":"en_US"},"meta":{"createDate":"Fri Mar 24 07:00:00 GMT 2023","lastModifiedDate":"Mon Mar 27 17:01:20 GMT 2023","publishedDate":"Mon Mar 27 17:01:20 GMT 2023","contentType":"book","archive":"false","ownerName":"apd migration","modifiedBy":"apd migration","version":"1","unPublished":false,"contentModel":"book"},"content":{"main":{"title":"macOS accessibility features for vision","summary":"Learn about macOS accessibility features for vision that make it easier to see or hear what’s on the Mac screen."},"sections":[{"level":"1","text":"<body dir=\"ltr\" id=\"mchl67c83f41\" class=\"AppleTopic apd-topic dark-mode-enabled\" data-istaskopen=\"true\" data-designversion=\"2\" lang=\"en\"><a name=\"mchl67c83f41\"></a><figure class=\"topicIcon\"><img src=\"https://help.apple.com/assets/63BCA927AAE78C58DD7FBE35/63BCA92EAAE78C58DD7FBE76/en_US/c3fdc62492cd63e79f2554926d6fbef0.png\" alt=\"\" height=\"30\" width=\"30\" originalImageName=\"SharedGlobalArt/AppIconTopic_Accessibility.png\"></figure><h1>macOS accessibility features for vision</h1><p>macOS includes accessibility features that make it easier to see what’s on the screen. You can also have your Mac speak what’s on the screen.</p><figure><img src=\"https://help.apple.com/assets/63BCA927AAE78C58DD7FBE35/63BCA92EAAE78C58DD7FBE76/en_US/5993fa7e17446c83c1c34c2c7c55eb36.png\" alt=\"A Pages document with the Hover Text window showing a high-resolution large version of text in the document.\" height=\"292\" width=\"466\" originalImageName=\"Art/S0083_HoverText.png\"></figure><div id=\"mchl648c3426\" class=\"Task\"><h2 aria-controls=\"aria-mchl648c3426\" class=\"Name\">VoiceOver</h2><div class=\"TaskBody\" role=\"region\" aria-hidden=\"false\" id=\"aria-mchl648c3426\"><p>Use VoiceOver, the built-in screen reader on your Mac, to speak what’s on the screen, and the text in documents, webpages, and windows. With VoiceOver, you can control your Mac with the keyboard, trackpad gestures, or a refreshable braille display. To customize VoiceOver, use VoiceOver Utility. See the <a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?product=voiceover&amp;locale=en_US&amp;type=ddm\" class=\"URL\">VoiceOver User Guide</a>.</p></div></div><div id=\"mchl5728dc43\" class=\"Task\"><h2 aria-controls=\"aria-mchl5728dc43\" class=\"Name\">Zoom features</h2><div class=\"TaskBody\" role=\"region\" aria-hidden=\"false\" id=\"aria-mchl5728dc43\"><ul><li><p>Make content on the screen larger and easier to see by zooming the entire screen or an area of it. If you’re using a second display, you can set the zoom for it separately. See <a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=change-zoom-settings-for-accessibility&amp;version=13.0&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=MH40579&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=13.0\" class=\"xRef AppleTopic\">Change Zoom settings for accessibility</a>.</p></li><li><p>Use Hover Text to zoom whatever is under the pointer—for example, text, fields, menu items, or buttons—in high resolution in a separate window. See <a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=use-hover-text&amp;version=13.0&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=MCHLB203BC78&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=13.0\" class=\"xRef AppleTopic\">Use Hover Text</a>.</p></li><li><p>If your Mac has a <a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=touch-bar&amp;version=13.0&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=GLOSBABD4062&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=13.0&amp;aside=true\" class=\"xRef Aside\">Touch Bar</a> and items in the Touch Bar are hard to see, turn on Touch Bar zoom to display a larger version of the Touch Bar on the screen. See <a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=zoom-in-on-the-touch-bar&amp;version=13.0&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=MCHL090BB3EE&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=13.0\" class=\"xRef AppleTopic\">Zoom in on the Touch Bar</a>.</p></li></ul></div></div><div id=\"mchla5022add\" class=\"Task\"><h2 aria-controls=\"aria-mchla5022add\" class=\"Name\">Display features</h2><div class=\"TaskBody\" role=\"region\" aria-hidden=\"false\" id=\"aria-mchla5022add\"><ul><li><p>Change the appearance of the screen by setting options to invert colors, reduce transparency, or use shapes to convey status information. You can also stop or reduce motion on the screen—for example, when you open apps. See <a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=change-display-settings-for-accessibility&amp;version=13.0&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=UNAC089&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=13.0\" class=\"xRef AppleTopic\">Change Display settings for accessibility</a>.</p></li><li><p>Make it easier to find the pointer on the screen by increasing its size or making it bigger only when you quickly move it, or by changing its color. See <a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=make-the-pointer-easier-to-see&amp;version=13.0&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=MCHLP2920&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=13.0\" class=\"xRef AppleTopic\">Make the pointer easier to see</a>.</p></li><li><p>Apply a color filter or tint to the screen to differentiate or tone down display colors. See <a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=change-display-colors-easier-onscreen&amp;version=13.0&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=MCHL11DDD4B3&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=13.0\" class=\"xRef AppleTopic\">Change display colors to make it easier to see what’s onscreen</a>.</p></li></ul></div></div><div id=\"mchl58f7577e\" class=\"Task\"><h2 aria-controls=\"aria-mchl58f7577e\" class=\"Name\">Spoken Content features</h2><div class=\"TaskBody\" role=\"region\" aria-hidden=\"false\" id=\"aria-mchl58f7577e\"><p>Customize the voice your Mac uses to speak text, and have your Mac speak announcements, items under the pointer, and whatever you type or select. See <a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=change-spoken-content-settings-accessibility&amp;version=13.0&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=SPCH638&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=13.0\" class=\"xRef AppleTopic\">Change Spoken Content settings for accessibility</a>.</p></div></div><div id=\"mchle175a3f9\" class=\"Task\"><h2 aria-controls=\"aria-mchle175a3f9\" class=\"Name\">Descriptions</h2><div class=\"TaskBody\" role=\"region\" aria-hidden=\"false\" id=\"aria-mchle175a3f9\"><p>Listen to a description of the visual content in movies, TV shows, and other media, if available. See <a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=change-descriptions-settings-accessibility&amp;version=13.0&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=MCHL2A14F1C5&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=13.0\" class=\"xRef AppleTopic\">Change Descriptions settings for accessibility</a>.</p></div></div><div class=\"LinkUniversal\"><strong>See also</strong><a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=get-started-with-accessibility-features&amp;version=13.0&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=MH35884&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=13.0\" class=\"xRef AppleTopic\">Get started with accessibility features on Mac</a><a href=\"https://support.apple.com/accessibility\" class=\"URL\">Apple Accessibility Support website</a></div></body>","tags":[{"type":"audience","refKey":"PUBLIC_USERS","tagPath":"audience/PUBLIC_USERS","title":"Public"}]}]},"categoryInfo":{"categories":["IP-Meta/DesignVersion/DesignVersion2","platform/mac","DisplayVersion/macOS Ventura 13","MetaFollow/MetaFollowOFF","ContentMode/liveContent","SupportSearchIndex/SupportSearchIndexON","ArchivalStatus/Archived","ExternalIndex/ExternalIndexOFF"],"categoryDictionaries":[{"key":"SupportSearchIndexON","name":"SupportSearchIndexON","englishName":"SupportSearchIndexON","displayName":"SupportSearchIndexON","articleCount":"120736"},{"key":"liveContent","name":"Live Content","englishName":"Live Content","displayName":"Live Content","articleCount":"135880"},{"key":"IP-Meta","name":"IP-Meta","englishName":"IP-Meta","displayName":"IP-Meta","articleCount":"0"},{"key":"ContentMode","name":"ContentMode","englishName":"ContentMode","displayName":"ContentMode","articleCount":"0"},{"key":"DesignVersion2","name":"DesignVersion 2","englishName":"DesignVersion 2","displayName":"DesignVersion 2","articleCount":"135315"},{"key":"MetaFollow","name":"MetaFollow","englishName":"MetaFollow","displayName":"MetaFollow","articleCount":"0"},{"key":"ExternalIndex","name":"ExternalIndex","englishName":"ExternalIndex","displayName":"ExternalIndex","articleCount":"0"},{"key":"DesignVersion","name":"DesignVersion","englishName":"DesignVersion","displayName":"DesignVersion","articleCount":"0"},{"key":"mac","name":"mac","englishName":"mac","displayName":"mac","articleCount":"85819"},{"key":"platform","name":"platform","englishName"